```julia
function add_yearmonth(df::DataFrame)
    return transform(df, :dt => ByRow((x -> string(Dates.year(x)) * "mm")) => :ym)
end
```

This function uses the `ByRow` transformation from the DataFrames.jl API to apply a anonymous function that extracts the year and month from each date time in the `dt` column and concatenates them together as an integer in the format "yyyymm". The result is a new DataFrame with an additional column named `ym`.
